	heroObjectPosition={`center 40%`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If your work is wearing you down, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> These Bible verses for work meet you where the pressure lives — the stress, the burnout, the identity fused to your career, the fear of failing or being let go. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on your phone — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "Bible verses for work," "scripture for work stress," or "verses about your job" — the answer starts in one place: your worth was never your title, your output, or your performance review. You are His beloved, off the clock and on, before you finish a single task.`}
	keyTakeaway={`You are not loved because you produce, perform, or climb the ladder. You are the Father's beloved child right now — not the résumé version of you. Your identity comes from Him, not from your job title, and He does not grade you by your output.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight workers carry`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you feel burned out, anxious about your job, or like you're only as valuable as what you produced this week, you are not weak and you are not alone. A whole generation of workers carries the same weight — and the numbers say it out loud.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `44%`, label: `of employees worldwide say they experienced a lot of daily stress — a record high (Gallup, State of the Global Workplace 2022)` },
		{ value: `21%`, label: `of workers are engaged at work; the vast majority feel disengaged or actively disengaged from their jobs (Gallup, State of the Global Workplace 2023)` },
		{ value: `77%`, label: `of workers reported work-related stress in the past month, and 57% reported negative impacts tied to stress like burnout (APA, Work and Well-Being Survey 2023)` },
		{ value: `Recognized`, label: `burnout is now classified as an 'occupational phenomenon' resulting from chronic, unmanaged workplace stress (World Health Organization, ICD-11)` },
