	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real person — maybe you. The inbox that's full again before you've finished your coffee. The Sunday-night dread. The sense that one missed deadline could erase everything you've built. The fear of the day the paycheck stops and you don't know who you are without the title on your business card.</p><p>None of this means something is wrong with you. It means you're human, living in a world that ties your value to your output and your job — and that's a weight no one was built to carry. There is a Father who sees the real you underneath the role, and He has something to say about who you actually are.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
		{ label: `Gallup — State of the Global Workplace Report`, url: `https://www.gallup.com/workplace/349484/state-of-the-global-workplace.aspx` },
