	]}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for your work`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what almost no one tells you in the middle of a hard week: the answer to the pressure isn't a better title, a bigger paycheck, or finally becoming the high performer you think you're supposed to be. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect, holy Father who already loves you, today, productive or not.</p><p>You were not made to earn your worth on the job. You were made to receive it. And the One who made you doesn't grade your performance, rank you against your coworkers, or love you more on the days you hit your numbers. He calls you His beloved child — not the promoted you, not the productive you, but <em>you</em>, right now, in the busy seasons and the slow ones and the long burnout.</p><p>So before you're an employee, a manager, a job title, a line on an org chart — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the steady voice underneath the noise of the workday, the one who says: I see you, I'm proud of you, and there is nothing you could do — no deadline you could hit or miss — to make Me love you more, or less.</p>`}
