		{ ref: `Ephesians 6:7`, slug: `ephesians`, ch: 6, text: `Serve wholeheartedly, as if you were serving your Father and not people.`, note: `Even the most ordinary task becomes worship when you do it for your Father.` },
		{ ref: `Proverbs 16:3`, slug: `proverbs`, ch: 16, text: `Commit whatever you do to your Father, and He will establish your plans.`, note: `Hand your work to Him each morning — your Father steadies what you can't control.` },
		{ ref: `Ecclesiastes 3:13`, slug: `ecclesiastes`, ch: 3, text: `That each person may eat and drink and find satisfaction in all their labor — this is the gift of your Father.`, note: `Finding genuine satisfaction in your work isn't earned; it's a gift your Father gives.` },
		{ ref: `Matthew 11:28-30`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 11, text: `Come to Me, all of you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest. Take My yoke upon you and learn from Me, for I am gentle and humble in heart, and you will find rest for your souls.`, note: `When the work has worn you out, your Father invites you to lay it down and breathe.` },
