		{ ref: `Proverbs 22:29`, slug: `proverbs`, ch: 22, text: `Do you see someone skilled in their work? They will serve before kings; they will not serve before officials of low rank.`, note: `Your Father honors faithful, skilled work — He sees and lifts up what diligence quietly builds.` },
		{ ref: `1 Corinthians 15:58`, slug: `1-corinthians`, ch: 15, text: `Stand firm. Let nothing move you. Always give yourselves fully to the work of your Father, because you know that your labor in Him is not in vain.`, note: `Nothing done for your Father is ever wasted, even when it feels like it disappears.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 90:17`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 90, text: `May the favor of your Father rest on us; establish the work of our hands for us — yes, establish the work of our hands.`, note: `Ask your Father to make your work matter; He delights to give your labor lasting purpose.` },
