	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for work?`, answer: `Colossians 3:23-24 (work as for the Lord), Ephesians 6:7 (serve wholeheartedly), Proverbs 16:3 (commit your work to Him), Ecclesiastes 3:13 (satisfaction in labor is a gift), Matthew 11:28-30 (come to Me, all who are weary), Genesis 2:15 (work was God's idea), and 1 Corinthians 15:58 (your labor is not in vain) all speak straight to what workers carry. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about hard work?`, answer: `The Bible honors diligence and skill — Proverbs 22:29 says the skilled worker will stand before kings, and Colossians 3:23 calls us to work wholeheartedly. But it never ties your worth to your output. Work is a gift from a Father (Ecclesiastes 3:13, Genesis 2:15), not a way to earn His love. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals the God behind those passages as a Father who delights in you, productive or not — read it free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a Bible verse for a stressful job?`, answer: `Matthew 11:28-30 is a favorite when work overwhelms you: 'Come to Me, all of you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest.' Proverbs 16:3 (commit your work to Him) and Philippians 4:6-7 are also steadying when the pressure mounts. You can read or listen to all of them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read — right on your lunch break or the commute home.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about work-life balance and rest?`, answer: `Rest is woven into creation itself — God rested on the seventh day and built a rhythm of work and rest into how we're made. Jesus invites the weary to come to Him for rest (Matthew 11:28-30), and Psalm 127 warns against anxiously overworking. The Bible treats rest not as laziness but as trust in a Father who provides. Meet that Father for yourself in the Father's Heart Bible™, free with audio at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio I can listen to at work?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book — perfect for the commute, a lunch break, or a sleepless night after a stressful day.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for work?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of reading one more voice telling you to perform, you meet the One who already delights in you. For someone under constant pressure to produce, that reframes everything: you come to the Bible as a loved child first, not an employee being graded. Read it free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
	]}
